Paper: hep-th/9302088

Date: 1993-02-19

Title: Quantum Chains with U_q(SL(2)) Symmetry and Unrestricted Representations

Authors: Daniel Arnaudon and Vladimir Rittenberg

Comments: 9 pages, minor TeXnical revision to allow automatic TeXing

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B306 (1993) 86-90

We consider two-state (q^2=-1) and three-state (q^3=1) one-dimensionalquantum spin chains with U_q(SL(2)) symmetry. Taking unrestrictedrepresentations (periodic, semi-periodic and nilpotent), we show which are thenecessary conditions to obtain a Hermitian Hamiltonian.